==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pondweed
<hw>Pond"weed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any aquatic plant of the genus <gen>Potamogeton</gen>, of which
many species are found in ponds or slow-moving rivers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Choke pondweed</b></col>, <cd>an American water weed
(<spn>Anarcharis Canadensis</spn>, syn. <spn>Elodea Canadensis</spn>.)
See <er>Anacharis</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Horned pondweed</b></col>,
<cd>the <spn>Zannichellia palustris</spn>, a slender, branching aquatic
plant, having pointed nutlets.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pone</ent>⟦br⟧
